{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Context\nThe plan-review gate (`5fd2`) reviews ONE ticket's plan in isolation. It deliberately does NOT detect SEMANTIC overlap, duplication, or undeclared dependencies BETWEEN SEPARATE tickets across the store. Existing coverage is partial and different in kind: `G4` checks consistency WITHIN one epic's children; `next_batch` schedules around DETERMINISTIC file-impact conflicts; `duplicates`/`supersedes` are MANUAL links. The residual — semantic overlap / duplication / hidden cross-ticket dependency across UNRELATED tickets — is uncovered.\n\n## Scope\nA store-wide overlap detector for the ticket UNDER PLAN REVIEW, comparing it against the whole store (cross-epic AND non-epic; any other ticket may overlap). It runs as a distinct STORE-WIDE step during the plan-review invocation window (before claim), NOT as a per-ticket `5fd2` criterion — a per-ticket reviewer cannot see the whole store, which is exactly why this is a separate step. It is ADVISORY ONLY and never affects the claim-gate verdict.\n\n## Design (plan of record — see the plan-of-record comment for full detail + research grounding)\nTwo-stage retrieve-then-rerank: (0) each ticket gets a cached, LLM-extracted Cupid digest (no embeddings, no vector DB); (1) brute-force BM25F over corpus digests narrows to ~20 candidates, excluding the query ticket's own graph; (2) a bounded LLM pairwise judge classifies each candidate and surfaces ≤3 advisory link suggestions for human confirmation. Enrichment is async via an event-sourced queue drained opportunistically (Tier 1). Full detail, decisions, and the ~6 subagent research reports are in the plan-of-record comment. Child stories S1–S7 implement it; Tier-2/Tier-3 drain and a Jira-reconciler drain are spun out as linked ideas.\n\n## Success Criteria\n- [ ] For the ticket under review, overlap is detected against ANY other ticket store-wide (cross-epic AND non-epic), beyond deterministic file-impact and manual links.\n- [ ] Candidate `duplicates`/`supersedes`/`depends_on` relations are surfaced for HUMAN confirmation (each with a ready-to-run `rebar link` command); the tool NEVER auto-mutates links. Rationale for suggestion-only: link semantics require human judgment of intent (duplicate vs. distinct-but-related), and a false auto-link corrupts the dependency graph that `ready`/`next_batch`/the completion gate depend on — a false suggestion costs one ignored line, a false auto-link costs silent graph corruption.\n- [ ] Low false-flagging of legitimately-related-but-distinct work: precision is measured on a labeled fixture of ticket pairs (see S6), and a related-but-distinct pair must not be surfaced.\n- [ ] It is a store-wide step run during the plan-review window, advisory-only, never blocking or altering the claim-gate verdict.\n- [ ] An ADR (docs/adr/) captures the architecture: Cupid-digest-without-embeddings, event-store-as-enrichment-queue, digest-as-REVIEW_RESULT-style-sidecar, and overlap-at-review-time-not-as-a-5fd2-criterion.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Detects semantic overlap/duplication between separate tickets store-wide (cross-epic AND non-epic), beyond deterministic file-impact and manual links (delivered across S1–S7).\n- [ ] Surfaces ≤3 candidate duplicate/supersede/dependency relations for human confirmation with copy-paste `rebar link` commands; does not auto-mutate links (S6, S7).\n- [ ] Runs as a store-wide step during the plan-review window; advisory-only; does NOT run as a `5fd2` per-ticket criterion and does NOT affect the claim-gate verdict (S7).\n- [ ] The architecture is captured in an ADR under docs/adr/.\n"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783572132120615001,"uuid":"aaef0448-def2-49a7-a9f6-43566b3f6f03"}